<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<!--
  ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
  ║  GitHub Repo Security Investigation — HTML Report Template      ║
  ║                                                                 ║
  ║  INSTRUCTIONS FOR LLM:                                          ║
  ║  1. Copy this entire file                                       ║
  ║  2. Replace all {{PLACEHOLDER}} values with real data            ║
  ║  3. For every <!-- EXAMPLE-START --> ... <!-- EXAMPLE-END --> pair:║
  ║       replace the content between the markers with real data,   ║
  ║       then DELETE both markers. Final file must satisfy         ║
  ║       `grep -c EXAMPLE- file.html` returning 0.                  ║
  ║  4. Choose verdict class: "critical", "caution", or "clean"      ║
  ║  5. Choose colors: "red", "amber", or "green" for score cells    ║
  ║  6. Save as: GitHub-Scanner-OWNER-REPO.html + matching .md file  ║
  ║                                                                 ║
  ║  RULES:                                                         ║
  ║  - No jargon without explanation                                 ║
  ║  - Every finding answers "what does this mean for ME?"           ║
  ║  - Write like you're advising a friend, not a security analyst   ║
  ║  - Be specific: PR numbers, dates, who submitted, who merged     ║
  ║  - If something is safe, say so plainly                          ║
  ║  - Scorecard consistency: if any finding is critical, no         ║
  ║    scorecard cell may be green. If hooks uninspected, "Is it    ║
  ║    safe out of the box?" must be amber at best.                  ║
  ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
-->
<title>Security Investigation: {{OWNER}}/{{REPO}}</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600;700&family=DM+Sans:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  /* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
     DESIGN SYSTEM — DO NOT MODIFY
     Dark theme, security monitoring aesthetic
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ */
  :root {
    --bg-void: #0a0a0c;
    --bg-surface: #131316;
    --bg-elevated: #1a1a1f;
    --bg-hover: #222228;
    --border: #32323c;
    --border-subtle: #26262e;
    --text-primary: #f0f0f4;
    --text-secondary: #b0b0bc;
    --text-muted: #7e7e8e;
    --red-glow: #ff4545;
    --red-dim: #ff454520;
    --red-bg: #1a0f0f;
    --amber-glow: #ffaa2a;
    --amber-dim: #ffaa2a20;
    --amber-bg: #1a150e;
    --green-glow: #22c55e;
    --green-dim: #22c55e20;
    --green-bg: #0e1a12;
    --cyan-glow: #06b6d4;
    --cyan-dim: #06b6d420;
    --font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    --font-sans: 'DM Sans', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
  }

  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

  body {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    background: var(--bg-void);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.65;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }

  /* Noise texture */
  body::before {
    content: '';
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    background: url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg viewBox='0 0 256 256' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cfilter id='n'%3E%3CfeTurbulence type='fractalNoise' baseFrequency='0.9' numOctaves='4' stitchTiles='stitch'/%3E%3C/filter%3E%3Crect width='100%25' height='100%25' filter='url(%23n)' opacity='0.03'/%3E%3C/svg%3E");
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 9999;
  }

  a { color: var(--cyan-glow); text-decoration: none; }
  a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

  /* Font size controls */
  .font-controls {
    position: fixed; top: 16px; right: 16px; z-index: 1000;
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 2px;
    background: var(--bg-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px; padding: 4px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.5); backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
  }
  .font-controls button {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700;
    width: 34px; height: 34px; border: none; border-radius: 6px;
    background: transparent; color: var(--text-secondary); cursor: pointer;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; transition: all 0.15s;
  }
  .font-controls button:hover { background: var(--bg-hover); color: var(--text-primary); }
  .font-controls button:active { transform: scale(0.92); }
  .font-controls .font-size-display {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-muted);
    min-width: 38px; text-align: center; letter-spacing: 0.05em; user-select: none;
  }

  .page { max-width: 960px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 20px; }

  /* Hero */
  .hero { padding: 64px 0 48px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); position: relative; }
  .hero::after {
    content: ''; position: absolute; bottom: -1px; left: 0; right: 0; height: 120px;
    background: linear-gradient(to top, var(--bg-void), transparent); pointer-events: none;
  }
  .hero-badge {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 20px;
    padding: 6px 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; background: var(--bg-surface);
  }
  .hero-badge .dot {
    width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--text-muted); /* Neutral default — LLM must set .red, .green, or .amber */
  }
  .hero-badge .dot.red { background: var(--red-glow); box-shadow: 0 0 8px var(--red-glow); animation: pulse 2s ease-in-out infinite; }
  .hero-badge .dot.green { background: var(--green-glow); box-shadow: 0 0 8px var(--green-glow); }
  .hero-badge .dot.amber { background: var(--amber-glow); box-shadow: 0 0 8px var(--amber-glow); animation: pulse 3s ease-in-out infinite; }
  @keyframes pulse { 0%, 100% { opacity: 1; } 50% { opacity: 0.4; } }
  .hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
    font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.03em; line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .hero h1 span { color: var(--red-glow); }
  .hero h1 span.green { color: var(--green-glow); }
  .hero h1 span.amber { color: var(--amber-glow); }
  .hero .meta { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-primary); display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 16px; }
  .hero .meta-item { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; }
  .hero .meta-item .label { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 12px; }

  /* Verdict */
  .verdict-section { padding: 48px 0 40px; }
  .verdict-banner { border-radius: 12px; padding: 32px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
  .verdict-banner.critical { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a0808 0%, #0a0a0c 100%); border: 1px solid #ff454540; }
  .verdict-banner.caution { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1508 0%, #0a0a0c 100%); border: 1px solid #ffaa2a40; }
  .verdict-banner.clean { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #081a0e 0%, #0a0a0c 100%); border: 1px solid #22c55e40; }
  .verdict-banner::before {
    content: ''; position: absolute; top: -50%; left: -50%; width: 200%; height: 200%;
  }
  .verdict-banner.critical::before { background: radial-gradient(circle at 30% 30%, #ff454508, transparent 50%); }
  .verdict-banner.caution::before { background: radial-gradient(circle at 30% 30%, #ffaa2a08, transparent 50%); }
  .verdict-banner.clean::before { background: radial-gradient(circle at 30% 30%, #22c55e08, transparent 50%); }
  .verdict-banner .verdict-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 12px; position: relative;
  }
  .verdict-banner.critical .verdict-label { color: var(--red-glow); }
  .verdict-banner.caution .verdict-label { color: var(--amber-glow); }
  .verdict-banner.clean .verdict-label { color: var(--green-glow); }
  .verdict-banner h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 3vw, 1.8rem); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.3;
    margin-bottom: 16px; position: relative; color: #ff8c00;
  }
  .verdict-banner.clean h2 { color: var(--green-glow); }

  /* Verdict bullet list */
  .verdict-bullets { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; position: relative; }
  .verdict-bullets li {
    display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 12px; font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--text-primary); line-height: 1.6; padding: 8px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #ffffff08;
  }
  .verdict-bullets li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .verdict-bullets .bullet-icon {
    flex-shrink: 0; width: 22px; height: 22px; border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 11px; margin-top: 2px;
  }
  .verdict-bullets .bullet-icon.red { background: var(--red-dim); color: var(--red-glow); box-shadow: 0 0 6px var(--red-dim); }
  .verdict-bullets .bullet-icon.amber { background: var(--amber-dim); color: var(--amber-glow); box-shadow: 0 0 6px var(--amber-dim); }
  .verdict-bullets .bullet-icon.green { background: var(--green-dim); color: var(--green-glow); box-shadow: 0 0 6px var(--green-dim); }

  /* Scorecard */
  .scorecard-section { padding: 0 0 48px; }
  .scorecard-grid {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 1px;
    background: var(--border); border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden;
  }
  .score-cell { background: var(--bg-surface); padding: 24px 20px; text-align: center; transition: background 0.2s; }
  .score-cell:hover { background: var(--bg-elevated); }
  .score-cell .score-icon {
    width: 32px; height: 32px; margin: 0 auto 12px; border-radius: 8px;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 16px;
  }
  .score-cell .score-icon.red { background: var(--red-dim); color: var(--red-glow); }
  .score-cell .score-icon.amber { background: var(--amber-dim); color: var(--amber-glow); }
  .score-cell .score-icon.green { background: var(--green-dim); color: var(--green-glow); }
  .score-cell .score-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .score-cell .score-value { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2; }
  .score-cell .score-value.red { color: var(--red-glow); }
  .score-cell .score-value.amber { color: var(--amber-glow); }
  .score-cell .score-value.green { color: var(--green-glow); }

  /* Collapsible sections */
  details summary { cursor: pointer; list-style: none; }
  details summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .collapsible-section > summary { padding: 48px 0 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle); }
  .collapsible-section > summary .section-header { margin-bottom: 0; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; }
  .collapsible-section[open] > summary .section-header { margin-bottom: 28px; }
  .collapsible-section .section-body { padding-bottom: 0; }
  .collapsible-section > summary .section-header::after {
    content: '\25B6'; font-size: 10px; color: var(--text-muted); transition: transform 0.2s; margin-left: auto;
  }
  .collapsible-section[open] > summary .section-header::after { transform: rotate(90deg); }
  .section-header .section-number {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--text-muted);
    width: 28px; height: 28px; border-radius: 6px; border: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .section-header h2 { font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }

  /* Finding cards */
  .finding-card {
    background: var(--bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 12px; overflow: hidden; transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }
  .finding-card:hover { border-color: #3a3a44; }
  .finding-card.critical { border-left: 3px solid var(--red-glow); }
  .finding-card.warning { border-left: 3px solid var(--amber-glow); }
  .finding-card.info { border-left: 3px solid var(--cyan-glow); }
  .finding-card.ok { border-left: 3px solid var(--green-glow); }
  @keyframes border-pulse {
    0%, 100% { border-left-color: var(--red-glow); box-shadow: -2px 0 8px var(--red-dim); }
    50% { border-left-color: #ff454580; box-shadow: -2px 0 4px transparent; }
  }
  .finding-card.critical { animation: border-pulse 3s ease-in-out infinite; }

  .finding-header {
    padding: 16px 20px 12px; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: baseline; gap: 8px 16px;
  }
  .finding-header .tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase; padding: 3px 8px; border-radius: 4px; font-weight: 600; flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .tag.critical-tag { background: var(--red-dim); color: var(--red-glow); }
  .tag.warning-tag { background: var(--amber-dim); color: var(--amber-glow); }
  .tag.info-tag { background: var(--cyan-dim); color: var(--cyan-glow); }
  .tag.ok-tag { background: var(--green-dim); color: var(--green-glow); }
  .finding-header .finding-date { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-secondary); }
  .finding-header .finding-duration {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--amber-glow); background: var(--amber-dim); border: 1px solid #ffaa2a30;
    padding: 3px 10px; border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .finding-header h3 { width: 100%; font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.4; margin-top: 4px; }

  /* Finding collapsible */
  .finding-card summary { list-style: none; cursor: pointer; }
  .finding-card summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .finding-card summary .finding-header { position: relative; padding-right: 40px; }
  .finding-card summary .finding-header::after {
    content: '\25B6'; font-size: 10px; color: var(--text-muted);
    transition: transform 0.2s; position: absolute; right: 20px; top: 20px;
  }
  .finding-card details[open] > summary .finding-header::after { transform: rotate(90deg); }

  .finding-body { padding: 0 20px 16px; }
  .finding-body p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-primary); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .finding-meta {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr)); gap: 8px; margin-top: 12px;
  }
  .meta-chip {
    font-size: 12px; padding: 8px 12px; border-radius: 6px;
    background: var(--bg-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2px;
  }
  .meta-chip .chip-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-secondary);
  }
  .meta-chip .chip-value { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 500; }

  /* Sub-finding (nested under parent finding) */
  .sub-finding {
    margin: 16px 0 8px; padding: 16px; border-left: 2px solid var(--amber-glow);
    background: var(--bg-elevated); border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
  }
  .sub-finding .sub-finding-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--amber-glow); margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .sub-finding h4 { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.4; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .sub-finding p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-primary); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 12px; }

  /* PR Table */
  .pr-table-wrap { overflow-x: auto; -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 13px; }
  th {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-secondary); text-align: left;
    padding: 12px 16px; background: var(--bg-surface); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    position: sticky; top: 0; white-space: nowrap;
  }
  td { padding: 14px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle); color: var(--text-primary); vertical-align: top; }
  tr:hover td { background: var(--bg-surface); }
  td:first-child { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-weight: 600; color: var(--cyan-glow); white-space: nowrap; }
  .td-concern { color: var(--amber-glow); font-weight: 500; }
  .td-reviewed-no { color: var(--red-glow); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-weight: 600; }
  .td-reviewed-yes { color: var(--green-glow); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-weight: 600; }
  .td-reviewed-rejected { color: var(--amber-glow); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-weight: 600; }
  .td-merge-fast { font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--red-glow); font-weight: 600; }
  .td-person { font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-primary); }

  /* Timeline */
  .timeline { position: relative; padding-left: 28px; }
  .timeline::before {
    content: ''; position: absolute; left: 7px; top: 8px; bottom: 8px; width: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--border), var(--red-glow), var(--border));
  }
  .tl-item { position: relative; margin-bottom: 20px; padding-left: 8px; }
  .tl-item::before {
    content: ''; position: absolute; left: -24px; top: 7px; width: 9px; height: 9px;
    border-radius: 50%; background: var(--text-muted); border: 2px solid var(--bg-void);
  }
  .tl-item.bad::before { background: var(--red-glow); box-shadow: 0 0 6px var(--red-dim); }
  .tl-item.good::before { background: var(--green-glow); }
  .tl-item.neutral::before { background: var(--amber-glow); }
  .tl-date { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-secondary); font-weight: 600; }
  .tl-desc { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-primary); margin-top: 2px; line-height: 1.6; }

  /* Vitals */
  .vitals-grid {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border-radius: 10px; overflow: hidden;
  }
  .vital-cell { background: var(--bg-surface); padding: 18px 20px; }
  .vital-cell .vital-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .vital-cell .vital-value { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .vital-cell .vital-note { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.5; }

  /* Action cards */
  .action-card { padding: 24px; border-radius: 10px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .action-card.stop { background: var(--red-bg); border: 1px solid #ff454530; }
  .action-card.wait { background: var(--amber-bg); border: 1px solid #ffaa2a30; }
  .action-card.info-action { background: var(--bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .action-card.ok-action { background: var(--green-bg); border: 1px solid #22c55e30; }
  .action-card h3 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .action-card p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-primary); line-height: 1.7; }

  /* Code blocks inside action cards */
  .action-card pre {
    background: var(--bg-void); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 16px; margin: 12px 0; overflow-x: auto;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; color: var(--cyan-glow); line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* Evidence Appendix — <pre> blocks for command and multi-line result */
  .evidence-row { margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .evidence-row .evidence-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .evidence-pre {
    background: var(--bg-void); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 12px 14px; margin: 0; overflow-x: auto; white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-word;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--cyan-glow); line-height: 1.55;
    max-height: 320px; overflow-y: auto;
  }
  .evidence-pre.result { color: var(--text-primary); }
  .evidence-classification {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-primary);
    padding: 8px 12px; background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle); border-radius: 6px;
  }
  .evidence-classification.inference { color: var(--amber-glow); }
  .evidence-classification.fact { color: var(--green-glow); }

  /* Footer */
  .footer {
    padding: 40px 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    text-align: center; font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-muted);
  }
  .footer a { color: var(--text-secondary); }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .scorecard-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
    .finding-meta { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero { padding: 40px 0 32px; }
    .collapsible-section > summary { padding-top: 32px; }
    table { font-size: 12px; }
    th, td { padding: 10px 12px; }
    .vitals-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 420px) {
    .scorecard-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="font-controls">
  <button onclick="adjustFont(-1)" title="Decrease font size" aria-label="Decrease font size">A&minus;</button>
  <span class="font-size-display" id="fontDisplay">100%</span>
  <button onclick="adjustFont(1)" title="Increase font size" aria-label="Increase font size">A+</button>
</div>
<script>
  let fontScale = 100;
  function adjustFont(dir) {
    fontScale = Math.min(150, Math.max(75, fontScale + dir * 10));
    document.documentElement.style.fontSize = fontScale + '%';
    document.getElementById('fontDisplay').textContent = fontScale + '%';
  }
</script>

<div class="page">

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
       HERO
       Replace {{OWNER}}, {{REPO}}, {{INVESTIGATION_DATE}}, etc.
       Dot: MUST set class="dot red", "dot amber", or "dot green" — default is gray (no verdict)
       h1 span: set class="red", "amber", or "green" to match verdict
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="hero-badge">
      <span class="dot red"></span><!-- REQUIRED: set "red", "amber", or "green" -->
      Security Investigation
    </div>
    <h1>{{OWNER}}/<span class="red">{{REPO}}</span></h1><!-- REQUIRED: set "red", "amber", or "green" -->
    <div class="meta">
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="label">Investigated</span> {{INVESTIGATION_DATE}}</div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="label">Applies to</span> {{VERSION_SCOPE}}</div><!-- e.g., "v1.6.0 (tag)" or "main @ abc1234" -->
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="label">Repo age</span> {{REPO_AGE}}</div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="label">Stars</span> {{STAR_COUNT}}</div>
      <div class="meta-item"><span class="label">License</span> {{LICENSE_TYPE}}</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
       VERDICT
       Use class: "critical" (red), "caution" (amber), or "clean" (green)
       Bullet icons: "red" with ✘, "amber" with ⚠, "green" with ✔
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="verdict-section">
    <div class="verdict-banner {{VERDICT_CLASS}}"><!-- critical | caution | clean -->
      <div class="verdict-label">Verdict</div>
      <h2>{{VERDICT_HEADLINE}}</h2>
      <ul class="verdict-bullets">
        <!-- EXAMPLE-START: replace with 5-8 real bullets, one finding each, plain English.
             Icon classes: "red" for dangerous, "amber" for concerning, "green" for safe.
             Icon characters: ✘ (&#x2718;) for red, ⚠ (&#x26A0;) for amber, ✔ (&#x2714;) for green. -->
        <li><span class="bullet-icon red">&#x2718;</span><span>Example: replace with a real finding</span></li>
        <li><span class="bullet-icon amber">&#x26A0;</span><span>Example: replace with a real finding</span></li>
        <li><span class="bullet-icon green">&#x2714;</span><span>Example: replace with a real finding</span></li>
        <!-- EXAMPLE-END -->
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
       SCORECARD
       4 cells. Each has DISTINCT placeholders — do NOT global-replace.
       Color class: "red", "amber", or "green" per cell.
       Labels: use the plain English versions shown below.
       Emoji suggestions: ⛔ &#x26D4; 🚨 &#x1F6A8; 🕶 &#x1F576; ⚠ &#x26A0; ✅ &#x2705;
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="scorecard-section">
    <div class="scorecard-grid">
      <div class="score-cell">
        <div class="score-icon {{REVIEW_COLOR}}">{{REVIEW_EMOJI}}</div>
        <div class="score-label">Does anyone check the code?</div>
        <div class="score-value {{REVIEW_COLOR}}">{{REVIEW_VALUE}}</div>
      </div>
      <div class="score-cell">
        <div class="score-icon {{RESPONSE_COLOR}}">{{RESPONSE_EMOJI}}</div>
        <div class="score-label">Do they fix problems quickly?</div>
        <div class="score-value {{RESPONSE_COLOR}}">{{RESPONSE_VALUE}}</div>
      </div>
      <div class="score-cell">
        <div class="score-icon {{TRANSPARENCY_COLOR}}">{{TRANSPARENCY_EMOJI}}</div>
        <div class="score-label">Do they tell you about problems?</div>
        <div class="score-value {{TRANSPARENCY_COLOR}}">{{TRANSPARENCY_VALUE}}</div>
      </div>
      <div class="score-cell">
        <div class="score-icon {{DEFAULTS_COLOR}}">{{DEFAULTS_EMOJI}}</div>
        <div class="score-label">Is it safe out of the box?</div>
        <div class="score-value {{DEFAULTS_COLOR}}">{{DEFAULTS_VALUE}}</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 01: WHAT SHOULD I DO?
       All sections start collapsed. Add "open" attribute to start expanded.
       Include action steps relevant to the verdict.
       For clean repos: use .ok-action cards with green headings.
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <details class="collapsible-section">
    <summary>
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-number">01</span>
        <h2>What Should I Do?</h2>
      </div>
    </summary>
    <div class="section-body">

    <!-- EXAMPLE-START: replace with real action steps. Classes: "stop" (red), "wait" (amber), "info-action" (neutral), "ok-action" (green).
         Dangerous repos: Steps 1-6 (stop, check exposure, rotate creds, update/remove, scan, AI prompt).
         Caution repos: Steps 1-3 (review findings, mitigate, monitor).
         Clean repos: one "ok-action" card saying "Safe to use" with any minor recommendations.
         IMPORTANT: each step needs BOTH a technical version (pre block) AND a non-technical version (plain English for non-terminal users). -->
    <div class="action-card stop">
      <h3 style="color:var(--red-glow)">Step 1: {{STEP_1_TITLE}}</h3>
      <p>{{STEP_1_DESCRIPTION_NONTECHNICAL}}</p>
      <pre>{{STEP_1_COMMANDS}}</pre>
    </div>
    <div class="action-card wait">
      <h3 style="color:var(--amber-glow)">Step 2: {{STEP_2_TITLE}}</h3>
      <p>{{STEP_2_DESCRIPTION_NONTECHNICAL}}</p>
    </div>
    <div class="action-card info-action">
      <h3>{{STEP_3_TITLE}}</h3>
      <p>{{STEP_3_DESCRIPTION}}</p>
    </div>
    <!-- EXAMPLE-END -->
    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 02: WHAT WE FOUND
       Each finding is a collapsible card.
       Card classes: "critical", "warning", "info", "ok"
       Tag classes: "critical-tag", "warning-tag", "info-tag", "ok-tag"
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <details class="collapsible-section">
    <summary>
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-number">02</span>
        <h2>What We Found</h2>
      </div>
    </summary>
    <div class="section-body">

    <!-- IF NO SIGNIFICANT FINDINGS: Replace ALL finding cards with this single card:
    <div class="finding-card ok">
      <div class="finding-header">
        <span class="tag ok-tag">OK</span>
        <h3>No significant security concerns found</h3>
      </div>
    </div>
    -->

    <!-- EXAMPLE-START: replace with one real finding card per finding. severity: critical | warning | info | ok -->
    <div class="finding-card {{SEVERITY}}"><!-- critical | warning | info | ok -->
      <details>
        <summary>
          <div class="finding-header">
            <span class="tag {{SEVERITY}}-tag">{{SEVERITY_LABEL}}</span><!-- Critical | Warning | Info | OK -->
            <span class="finding-date">{{DATE_RANGE}}</span>
            <span class="finding-duration">{{DURATION_OR_STATUS}}</span>
            <h3>{{FINDING_TITLE_PLAIN_ENGLISH}}</h3>
          </div>
        </summary>
        <div class="finding-body">
          <p>{{EXPLANATION_WHAT_THIS_MEANS_FOR_USER}}</p>
          <div class="finding-meta">
            <!-- PATTERN: Meta chips — include all that apply -->
            <div class="meta-chip">
              <span class="chip-label">Reported by</span>
              <span class="chip-value">{{WHO}} &mdash; <a href="https://github.com/{{OWNER}}/{{REPO}}/issues/{{NUM}}">Issue #{{NUM}}</a></span>
            </div>
            <div class="meta-chip">
              <span class="chip-label">Fixed by</span>
              <span class="chip-value">{{WHO}} &mdash; <a href="https://github.com/{{OWNER}}/{{REPO}}/pull/{{NUM}}">PR #{{NUM}}</a></span>
            </div>
            <div class="meta-chip">
              <span class="chip-label">Merged by</span>
              <span class="chip-value">{{WHO}}</span>
            </div>
            <div class="meta-chip">
              <span class="chip-label">Reviewed by</span>
              <span class="chip-value" style="color:var(--red-glow)">Nobody</span><!-- or remove style for normal color -->
            </div>
            <div class="meta-chip">
              <span class="chip-label">The fix</span>
              <span class="chip-value">{{WHAT_WAS_CHANGED}}</span>
            </div>
            <!-- END Meta chips -->
          </div>

          <!-- OPTIONAL: Sub-finding — nest related findings under their parent -->
          <div class="sub-finding">
            <div class="sub-finding-label">Related</div>
            <h4>{{SUB_FINDING_TITLE}}</h4>
            <p>{{SUB_FINDING_EXPLANATION}}</p>
            <div class="finding-meta">
              <div class="meta-chip">
                <span class="chip-label">{{LABEL}}</span>
                <span class="chip-value">{{VALUE}}</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- END Sub-finding -->

        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
    <!-- EXAMPLE-END -->

    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 02A: EXECUTABLE FILE INVENTORY (REQUIRED IF ANY EXEC FILES EXIST)
       One card per file that runs code: hooks, install/uninstall scripts,
       package lifecycle scripts (pre/postinstall), CI workflows, Dockerfiles,
       session/event handlers, background processes. Based on Step C in prompt.
       EVERY slot must be filled. Empty slots = investigation incomplete.
       If a property is "none observed", state that explicitly — don't leave blank.
       IF NO EXECUTABLE FILES EXIST: replace all cards with a single <p> stating
       "No executable files found in this repo (no hooks, scripts, workflows, or Dockerfile)."
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <details class="collapsible-section">
    <summary>
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-number">02A</span>
        <h2>Executable File Inventory</h2>
      </div>
    </summary>
    <div class="section-body">
    <p style="color:var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom:16px; font-size:14px">One card per executable file (hooks, install/uninstall scripts, package lifecycle scripts, CI workflows, Dockerfile, session/event handlers, background processes). Each card documents 7 properties derived from grep — NOT from the file's self-description — plus a capability assessment of what the code could do in the worst case.</p>

    <!-- EXAMPLE-START: delete this entire card block and replace with one real card per executable file. -->
    <div class="finding-card warning" style="margin-bottom:12px">
      <details>
        <summary>
          <div class="finding-header">
            <span class="tag warning-tag">Executable</span>
            <h3><code>{{FILE_PATH}}</code></h3>
          </div>
        </summary>
        <div class="finding-body">
          <div class="finding-meta">
            <div class="meta-chip">
              <span class="chip-label">1. Trigger</span>
              <span class="chip-value">{{WHEN_IT_RUNS}}</span><!-- e.g., "SessionStart hook — runs every Claude Code prompt" -->
            </div>
            <div class="meta-chip">
              <span class="chip-label">2. Reads</span>
              <span class="chip-value">{{FILES_AND_ENV_VARS_READ}}</span><!-- grep hits for readFile/read_text/open/os.environ/process.env -->
            </div>
            <div class="meta-chip">
              <span class="chip-label">3. Writes</span>
              <span class="chip-value">{{FILES_WRITTEN_AND_MODES}}</span><!-- grep hits for writeFile/fs.write/os.chmod -->
            </div>
            <div class="meta-chip">
              <span class="chip-label">4. Network</span>
              <span class="chip-value">{{NETWORK_HOSTS_OR_NONE}}</span><!-- list literal domains/hosts, or "none observed" -->
            </div>
            <div class="meta-chip">
              <span class="chip-label">5. Injection channel</span>
              <span class="chip-value">{{INPUT_TO_OUTPUT_FLOW_OR_NONE}}</span><!-- e.g., "reads user prompt, emits context text" or "none observed" -->
            </div>
            <div class="meta-chip">
              <span class="chip-label">6. Secret-leak path</span>
              <span class="chip-value">{{SECRETS_PLUS_SINK_OR_NONE}}</span><!-- secrets grep + logging/network in same file, or "none observed" -->
            </div>
            <div class="meta-chip">
              <span class="chip-label">7. Privilege</span>
              <span class="chip-value">{{USER_OR_ELEVATED_OR_SANDBOX}}</span><!-- "user-level", "sudo required", "writes to /etc, /usr/local, ~/.ssh" -->
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="sub-finding">
            <div class="sub-finding-label">Capability assessment</div>
            <p>{{WHAT_THIS_CODE_COULD_DO_WORST_CASE}}</p><!-- one paragraph synthesizing the 7 properties. Distinct from what it DOES. Example: "This hook could exfiltrate any file the user can read, since it has fs.readFileSync with a user-controlled path AND has network.fetch calls." -->
          </div>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
    <!-- EXAMPLE-END -->

    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 03: SUSPICIOUS CODE CHANGES
       Table of security-relevant PRs.
       All PR numbers link to: https://github.com/OWNER/REPO/pull/NUMBER
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <details class="collapsible-section">
    <summary>
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-number">03</span>
        <h2>Suspicious Code Changes</h2>
      </div>
    </summary>
    <div class="section-body">
    <div class="pr-table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>PR</th>
            <th>What it did</th>
            <th>Submitted by</th>
            <th>Merged by</th>
            <th>Reviewed?</th>
            <th>Merge time</th>
            <th>Concern</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <!-- EXAMPLE-START: one row per suspicious PR.
               IF NO SUSPICIOUS PRS: replace the entire table with:
               <p style="color:var(--text-secondary);padding:20px">No suspicious security-relevant PRs were identified in the sample reviewed.</p> -->
          <tr>
            <td><a href="https://github.com/{{OWNER}}/{{REPO}}/pull/{{NUM}}">#{{NUM}}</a></td>
            <td>{{PLAIN_ENGLISH_DESCRIPTION}}</td>
            <td class="td-person">{{AUTHOR}}</td>
            <td class="td-person">{{MERGER}}</td>
            <td class="td-reviewed-no">No</td><!-- or td-reviewed-yes / td-reviewed-rejected -->
            <td class="td-merge-fast">{{TIME}}</td><!-- use td-merge-fast class for suspiciously fast merges -->
            <td class="td-concern">{{WHY_SUSPICIOUS}}</td>
          </tr>
          <!-- EXAMPLE-END -->
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 04: TIMELINE
       Chronological events. Classes: "bad" (red dot), "good" (green), "neutral" (amber)
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <details class="collapsible-section">
    <summary>
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-number">04</span>
        <h2>Timeline</h2>
      </div>
    </summary>
    <div class="section-body">
    <div class="timeline">
      <!-- EXAMPLE-START: one tl-item per chronological event.
           class: "tl-item bad" (red), "tl-item good" (green), or "tl-item neutral" (amber). -->
      <div class="tl-item bad">
        <div class="tl-date">{{EVENT_DATE}}</div>
        <div class="tl-desc">{{EVENT_DESCRIPTION_PLAIN_ENGLISH}}</div>
      </div>
      <!-- EXAMPLE-END -->
    </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 05: REPO VITALS
       Grid of key metrics. Color the .vital-value with inline style
       for red/amber items: style="color:var(--red-glow)" or --amber-glow or --green-glow
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <details class="collapsible-section">
    <summary>
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-number">05</span>
        <h2>Repo Vitals</h2>
      </div>
    </summary>
    <div class="section-body">
    <div class="vitals-grid">
      <!-- EXAMPLE-START: one vital-cell per metric. Include 6-10 metrics. Omit inline style for neutral. -->
      <div class="vital-cell">
        <div class="vital-label">{{METRIC_NAME}}</div>
        <div class="vital-value" style="color:var(--{{COLOR}}-glow)">{{VALUE}}</div>
        <div class="vital-note">{{PLAIN_ENGLISH_INTERPRETATION}}</div>
      </div>
      <!-- EXAMPLE-END -->
    </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 06: INVESTIGATION COVERAGE (REQUIRED)
       This section is mandatory on every report. It tells the reader
       how thorough the investigation was and what data was missing.
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <details class="collapsible-section">
    <summary>
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-number">06</span>
        <h2>Investigation Coverage</h2>
      </div>
    </summary>
    <div class="section-body">
    <div class="vitals-grid">
      <!-- Fill in every cell with real data. Mark failed/blocked sources clearly. -->
      <div class="vital-cell">
        <div class="vital-label">Merged PRs reviewed</div>
        <div class="vital-value">{{REVIEWED_PR_COUNT}} of {{TOTAL_PR_COUNT}}</div>
        <div class="vital-note">{{PR_COVERAGE_NOTE}}</div><!-- e.g., "Sampled most recent 300" or "All PRs reviewed" -->
      </div>
      <div class="vital-cell">
        <div class="vital-label">Suspicious PR diffs read</div>
        <div class="vital-value">{{DIFFS_READ_COUNT}}</div>
        <div class="vital-note">PRs matching security keywords had their actual code changes reviewed</div>
      </div>
      <div class="vital-cell">
        <div class="vital-label">Dependency scan</div>
        <div class="vital-value" style="color:var(--{{DEP_SCAN_COLOR}}-glow)">{{DEP_SCAN_STATUS}}</div>
        <div class="vital-note">{{DEP_SCAN_NOTE}}</div><!-- e.g., "Blocked — requires admin access" or "3 alerts found" -->
      </div>
      <div class="vital-cell">
        <div class="vital-label">Workflow files read</div>
        <div class="vital-value">{{WORKFLOWS_READ_COUNT}}</div>
        <div class="vital-note">CI/CD workflow YAML files inspected for malicious steps</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- EXAMPLE-START: one card per failed/limited data source. DELETE the block entirely if all commands succeeded. -->
    <div class="finding-card info" style="margin-top:12px">
      <div class="finding-header">
        <span class="tag info-tag">Gap</span>
        <h3>{{WHAT_FAILED_OR_WAS_LIMITED}}</h3>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- EXAMPLE-END -->

    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 07: EVIDENCE APPENDIX (REQUIRED)
       Maps each major claim to the command run and result observed.
       This is what makes the report defensible.
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <details class="collapsible-section">
    <summary>
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-number">07</span>
        <h2>Evidence Appendix</h2>
      </div>
    </summary>
    <div class="section-body">
    <p style="color:var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom:16px; font-size:14px">Each major claim in this report is backed by a command and an observed result. Inferences are marked as such.</p>

    <!-- EXAMPLE-START: one card per major claim. Required for every critical finding,
         every warning finding, every failed/blocked command that limited the review,
         every major scorecard assertion (e.g., "0.3% review rate" needs an entry). -->
    <div class="finding-card info" style="margin-bottom:12px">
      <div class="finding-header">
        <span class="tag info-tag">Evidence</span>
        <h3>{{CLAIM_STATEMENT}}</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="finding-body">
        <div class="evidence-row">
          <div class="evidence-label">Command</div>
          <pre class="evidence-pre">{{COMMAND_RUN_VERBATIM}}</pre>
        </div>
        <div class="evidence-row">
          <div class="evidence-label">Result observed</div>
          <pre class="evidence-pre result">{{COMMAND_RESULT_VERBATIM_NOT_PARAPHRASED}}</pre><!-- Preserve newlines. Truncate with [...] if very long, but keep enough to show the point. -->
        </div>
        <div class="evidence-row">
          <div class="evidence-label">Classification</div>
          <div class="evidence-classification {{FACT_OR_INFERENCE_CLASS}}">{{CONFIRMED_FACT_OR_INFERENCE_WITH_NOTE}}</div><!-- class: "fact" for Confirmed fact, "inference" for Inference (include reason) -->
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- EXAMPLE-END -->

    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- ═══════════════ FOOTER ═══════════════ -->
  <div class="footer">
    Generated by <a href="https://github.com/stefans71/stop-git-std">stop-git-std</a> deep dive &middot; {{INVESTIGATION_DATE}}
    <br>This report is an automated investigation, not a professional security audit. It may miss issues. If you are making a business decision, consult a security professional.
  </div>

</div>

</body>
</html>
